## CSS RULES — MANDATORY

### CSS Namespacing
Each component uses a unique prefix. Never leak styles globally.
```
hp-    Home                    gw-    CRMGateway
ent-   Enterprise (shared)     vp-    VIPPortal
dev-   Developers (extends ent) ap-   AhmedPortal
re-    RealEstate (extends ent) mp-   MarketplacePortal
db-    Dashboard
```
Shared Enterprise base: `styles/ent-base.css` — only works on pages using `.ent-page` scope.
Automotive and other pages with own scope prefixes need their own CSS — do NOT attempt cross-scope sharing.

### CSS Logical Properties (RTL Support)
```css
/* ✅ DO — works in both LTR and RTL */
margin-inline-start: 1rem;
padding-inline-end: 0.5rem;
border-inline-start: 2px solid;
inset-inline-start: 0;
text-align: start;

/* ❌ DON'T — breaks in RTL */
margin-left: 1rem;
padding-right: 0.5rem;
border-left: 2px solid;
left: 0;
text-align: left;
```

### Responsive: Mobile-first
```css
.container { padding-inline: 1rem; }                              /* Mobile base */
@media (min-width: 768px) { .container { padding-inline: 2rem; } } /* Tablet */
@media (min-width: 1024px) { .container { max-width: 1200px; margin-inline: auto; } } /* Desktop */
```
Test at: 375px, 768px, 1024px, 1440px.

