## i18n — BILINGUAL (EN/AR)

### Active System
`src/i18n/pages/*.js` + `src/i18n/portals/*.js` — per-page modules.

```jsx
// Register translations (once per page, at import):
import { registerTranslations } from '../../i18n';
registerTranslations('pageName', { en: {...}, ar: {...} });

// Use in component:
import { useTranslation } from '../../i18n';
const { t } = useTranslation('pageName');
return <h1>{t('hero.title')}</h1>;
```

- Shared strings: `src/i18n/common.js`
- LanguageContext: detects browser language, persists to localStorage, sets `document.dir` + `document.lang`
- Arabic: Modern Standard Arabic, professional tone
- ALL form labels, select options, and user-facing strings MUST go through `t()` — never hardcoded

### DEPRECATED — Do Not Use
`src/translations/*.json` — legacy duplicate files. Never import from these.

---

## FIREBASE / FIRESTORE

### Collections
| Collection | Read | Write | Purpose |
|-----------|------|-------|---------|
| `smartcards` | Public | Admin only | NFC card profiles (status, redirectUrl, totalTaps) |
| `cards` | Public | Auth required | Digital card profiles — DO NOT modify structure |
| `taps` | Admin only | Create: public | NFC tap event log (append-only, never update/delete) |
| `behaviors` | Admin only | Create: public | Behavioral tracking (append-only) |
| `campaigns` | Auth required | Auth required | Marketing campaigns |
| `admins` | Admin only | Console only | Admin email whitelist (chain check) |
| `settings` | Auth required | Auth required | System configuration + scoring |
| `walletPassRequests` | — | — | Triggers `onWalletPassRequest` Cloud Function |
| `walletPasses` | — | — | Google Wallet save URLs |

### Composite Indexes
- `taps` → (cardId ASC, timestamp DESC)
- `taps` → (campaignId ASC, timestamp DESC)
- `behaviors` → (cardId ASC, timestamp ASC/DESC)

### Rules
- Always add `.limit()` to Firestore queries — prevent runaway reads
- Import `db` from `../../firebase.js`
- Admin check: `useAdmin()` hook queries `admins` collection by email

---

## CLOUD FUNCTIONS (`functions/index.js`)

| Function | Trigger | Purpose |
|----------|---------|---------|
| `cardRedirect` | HTTPS `/c/:cardId` | NFC tap → Firestore log + 302 redirect |
| `api` | HTTPS Express | Smartcards CRUD, taps/stats, campaigns, seed-demo (Bearer token auth) |
| `onWalletPassRequest` | Firestore `walletPassRequests/{docId}` onCreate | Creates Google Wallet pass |

---

## REACT PATTERNS

### Components
- Always functional components with hooks — never class components
- PascalCase filenames: `CardFlip.jsx`, `TapStats.jsx`
- Hooks: camelCase with `use` prefix: `useCardForm.js`
- Keep components focused — one responsibility per component
- Components over 500 lines: split into sub-components
- Define section components as `{SectionIdentity()}` not `<SectionIdentity />` inside render (prevents unmount/remount on every keystroke)
- Self-contained: each page folder has its own components/hooks/styles — avoid fragile cross-page shared imports

### State Management
- Local UI state: `useState`
- 3+ related states: extract to custom hook
- Global state: React Context (AuthContext, LanguageContext)
- No Redux, no Zustand, no MobX

### Admin Layout
`key={location.pathname}` on `<Outlet />` in AdminLayout.jsx is REQUIRED to prevent blank pages on first navigation.

---

## STRICT RULES — NEVER DO

1. NEVER modify `functions/index.js` without explicit request
2. NEVER modify `firebase.js` — production config
3. NEVER modify `App.jsx` routing without explicit request
4. NEVER modify `backend/` folder — Spring Boot is fully deprecated
5. NEVER modify `cards` Firestore collection structure
6. NEVER use or import from `src/translations/*.json` — legacy files
7. NEVER modify `blinq-app.shared.423b915ad.min.css` — legacy (audit pending)
8. NEVER use fake metrics (47%, 3.2×, 100%) — use qualitative: Named, Intent, Real-Time, Zero Guesswork
9. NEVER hardcode form labels — always use `t('key')` from i18n
10. NEVER call the product a "digital business card" — it is a "VIP Access Key"
11. NEVER use "Jane Doe" or "John Smith" — deprecated persona names
12. NEVER link demo buttons to individual portals from industry pages — link to dashboards
13. NEVER use font-weight below 400
14. NEVER use text opacity below 0.58
15. NEVER use "Real Estate" alone — always "Real Estate Developers & Agents"
16. NEVER leave `console.log` in code
17. NEVER use broken `href="#"` links

## STRICT RULES — ALWAYS DO

1. Always use CSS prefix per page (`hp-`, `ent-`, `dev-`, `gw-`, etc.)
2. Always use `db` named export from `firebase.js`
3. Always use `useAuth()` for auth, `useAdmin()` for admin check
4. Always run `npm run build` before deploy — build must pass
5. Always deploy from project ROOT (not frontend/)
6. Always use explicit `color: #FFFFFF` for white text on dark backgrounds
7. Always add `.limit()` to Firestore queries
8. Always wrap animations in `@media (prefers-reduced-motion: no-preference)`
9. Always test responsive at 375px, 768px, 1024px, 1440px

